[The news report says that the diagnosis of leptospirosis was "confirmed" clinically in most patients, implying that the diagnosis was not based on laboratory testing. Because of the relatively nonspecific nature of the clinical presentation of the leptospirosis, that is, many of the symptoms and signs can also be seen with other diseases, the diagnosis of leptospirosis cannot be made confidently without laboratory confirmation. In the US, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention can provide _Leptospira_ Dip-S-Tick (DST) IgM dot-ELISA test kits (PanBio Integrated Diagnostics) to local laboratories for serological testing of suspected leptospirosis cases in support of the response to a disaster (http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC149700/). The DST is suitable for in-the-field testing of suspected patients. Confirmatory testing uses the microscopic agglutination test (MAT).

Pathanamthitta is a city and capital of Pathanamthitta district, with a population of 37 538 residents, located in the Central Travancore region in the state of Kerala, southern India (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathanamthitta). A map of this area can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Pathanamthitta,+Kerala,+India. - Mod.ML

